{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC22"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc22-10074-whats-new-in-appkit"]}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc22\/10074","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (22 min)"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Discover the latest advances in Mac app development using AppKit. We’ll take you through the latest updates to SF Symbols, show you how you can elevate your interface with enhanced controls, and help you learn to coordinate your windows with Stage Manager. We’ll also explore the latest sharing and collaboration features for macOS."}],"metadata":{"title":"What’s new in AppKit","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC22","role":"sampleCode"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC22-10074-Whats-new-in-AppKit"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Stage-Manager","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Stage Manager"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC22-10074-stage-manager","type":"image"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Keeps the workspace tidy"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cleans up inactive windows in your workspace by showing only the active window"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Active window takes ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"center stage","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Pull windows together into sets which swap in and out as a group","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"IMPACTS on how your windows present themselves"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Newly presented windows ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"replace those on stage"}]}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Auxiliary windows cohabitate with primary windows (panels, popovers, settings)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default: Wont swap out IF you present"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"floating panels","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"modal window,"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"window with a preference style toolbar","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A window’s collection behaviour is respected. ("},{"code":"collectionBehavior","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If a window’s collection behavior is","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".auxiliary"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".moveToActiveSpace"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":".stationary","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":".transient","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Wont displace the active window in center stage.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"System Preferences (now ‘System Settings’)","anchor":"System-Preferences-now-System-Settings"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC22-10074-system-settings"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"refreshed navigation scheme"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"aligns with iOS"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Existing custom preference panes need no change."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Adopt the new styles when you’re ready, or not at all.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"New interface style for all configuration options with a new design language."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Best way to adopt the new style is with SwiftUI.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"What about AppKit?","anchor":"What-about-AppKit"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Suggests incremental adoption of SwiftUI into your existing app."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note - no indication of how to do this in AppKit directly.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc22\/10075","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" WWDC22"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"How?","anchor":"How"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create a form, set the formStyle ","type":"text"},{"code":".grouped","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to get the new style","type":"text"}]},{"code":["enum AirDropVisbility: String, CaseIterable, Identifiable {","    case nobody = \"No One\"","    case contactsOnly = \"Contacts Only\"","    case everyone = \"Everyone\"","","    var id: String { rawValue }","    var label: String { rawValue }","    var symbolName: String {","        switch self {","        case .nobody: return \"person.crop.circle.badge.xmark\"","        case .contactsOnly: return \"person.2.circle\"","        case .everyone: return \"person.crop.circle.badge.checkmark\"","        }","    }","}","","struct ExampleFormView: View {","    @State private var name: String = \"Mac Studio\"","    @State private var screenSharingEnabled: Bool = true","    @State private var fileSharingEnabled: Bool = false","    @State private var airdropVisibility = AirDropVisbility.contactsOnly","","    var body: some View {","        Form {","            TextField(\"Computer Name\", text: $name)","            Toggle(\"Screen Sharing\", isOn: $screenSharingEnabled)","            Toggle(\"File Sharing\", isOn: $fileSharingEnabled)","            Picker(\"AirDrop\", selection: $airdropVisibility) {","                ForEach(AirDropVisbility.allCases) {","                    Label($0.label, systemImage: $0.symbolName)","                        .labelStyle(.titleAndIcon)","                        .tag($0)","                }","            }","        }","        .formStyle(.grouped)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"In-app ‘Preferences’ have been renamed to ‘Settings’","anchor":"In-app-Preferences-have-been-renamed-to-Settings"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When building against macOS 13 SDK AppKit will automatically rename ‘Preferences’ in App menu to ‘Settings’"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You should update your own code to use ‘Settings’ instead of ‘Preferences’ wherever else"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Controls","anchor":"Controls"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"NSComboButton (new!)","anchor":"NSComboButton-new"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Immediate button action with a menu containing additional options"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Traditionally created using an NSSegmentedControl.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two styles :"}]},{"level":4,"type":"heading","text":"split","anchor":"split"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"separate arrow portion just for the menu","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC22-10074-nscombobutton-split","type":"image"}]},{"level":4,"type":"heading","text":"unified","anchor":"unified"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Primary action on click, menu action with click and hold.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC22-10074-nscombobutton-unified","type":"image"}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"NSColorWell","anchor":"NSColorWell"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC22-10074-nscolorwell","type":"image"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Default color well has new look. No adoption required - will just happen."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Two new styles (along with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"default"},{"text":")","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"minimal","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": shows a disclosure arrow on rollover - shows popover with palette of colors."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can customize the popover content (e.g., for a different palette, or to display a menu)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"expanded"}]},{"text":": color picker like in the iWork apps, with both disclosure arrow and color picker button","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can customize the popover content (e.g., for a different palette, or to display a menu)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"These are set using the new property ","type":"text"},{"code":"colorWellStyle","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"New target\/action pair for its action. If nil, uses system standard behaviour.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"NSToolBar","anchor":"NSToolBar"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"toolbarImmovableItemIdentifiers","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" - set toolbar items that ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"cannot"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" be moved or removed by the user","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"canBeInsertedAt"},{"type":"text","text":" - veto power of any particular reordering, insertion or removal from the toolbar (eg. for example, you could create a toolbar item that’s allowed within one section of the toolbar, but it’s disallowed within another section.)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"centeredItemIdentifiers"},{"type":"text","text":" - multiple centered items for the toolbar. Can only be moved within the center group"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"possibleLabels","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" - provides a set of labels so NSToolbarItem will size to fit the maximum label length","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"NSAlert (with long text)","anchor":"NSAlert-with-long-text"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Long text alerts will now use a new wider style (reminiscent of older NSAlert layout)."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Also if accessory view for the alert is too big for compact mode."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Happens automatically when the text is over a certain length. No coding change required."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"u